### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

```
export class SystemTableComponent {

  isLoading = signal(true);

  dataStream$ = new BehaviorSubject<null>(null);

  dataStreamObservable = this.dataStream$.pipe(
    tap((_) => {
      this.isLoading.set(true);
    })
  )
}

constructor(private state: StateService) {
  effect(() => {
    this.state.gatewayUrl();
    this.dataStream$.next(null);
  });
 }
}
```

Service:

```
export class StateService {
  env = signal<string>(
    localStorage.getItem('env') || environment['defaultEnv']
  );

  gatewayUrl = computed<string>(
    () => UrlMapping[this.env()] + 'gateway/v1/graphql'
  );

  gatewayChanged$ = new Subject<null>();

  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      // Subscribe to gatewayUrl changes
      this.gatewayUrl();
      // Trigger gatewayChanged event
      this.gatewayChanged$.next(null);
    });
  }
}
```

2 different signals that are not related throws writable constraints error.

> 0600: Writing to signals is not allowed in a `computed` or an `effect` by default.

Even when subscribing to the `gatewayChanged$` subject the same error shows up
```

    this.state.gatewayChanged$.pipe(takeUntilDestroyed()).subscribe({
      next: (_) => {
        this.pageIndex = 0;
        this.dataStream$.next(null);
      },
    });
```

